The evidence with the title 'What did the 2008–10 tax stimulus acts do? | Tax Policy Center ' says A one-year extension of the alternative minimum tax (amt) “ patch ” temporarily raised the AMT exemption . The cost: about $70 billion over 10 years. The patch saved affected taxpayers an estimated average of about $ 2,400 .Under permanent AMT law , roughly 30 million taxpayers would have owed the additional levy  ... 
